# Searching cursorignored folders

Some cursorignored folders contain context that is critical for making correct
decisions, even though they are not indexed for performance reasons.

## When to explicitly read from ignored paths

- **`docs/old/`** and **`docs/plans/archived/`** — completed plans and
  historical analyses. Read when context about past decisions is needed.
- **`.cursor/migration-archive/`** — STOR_MIGRATION analysis and agent
  transcripts. Read when discussing repo separation strategy.
- **`src/lib/gen/scaffolds/scaffold-embeddings.json`** and
  **`src/lib/gen/template-library/template-library.generated.json`** — large
  generated files. Do not read whole files; use the READMEs in those
  directories instead.
- **`Scripts/`** — dev runner and DB/migration entrypoints. `README.md`, `*.mjs`,
  and `*.ts` files are now indexed; only subdirs and non-code assets stay ignored.
  **`config/scripts/`** — offline helpers (docs embeddings, eval, audits).
  `README.md` and `*.ts` files are indexed.
- **`src/lib/gen/preview/shims.ts`** — preview import-shims (70 kB). Now indexed
  so agents can search/reference it directly when debugging preview render errors.

## How to search

Use explicit file paths with the Read tool. Cursorignored files are not
findable via semantic search or grep — you must know the path.

Use the READMEs placed in cursorignored directories as entry points:
- `src/lib/gen/data/README.md`
- `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/README.md`
- `src/lib/gen/template-library/README.md`
